--- Disjoint pair sources at n=6 ---
  A 3-cycle uses 3 of 6 vertices.
  A 5-cycle uses 5 of 6 vertices.
  3+3=6: disjoint iff complementary.
  3+5=8>6: ALWAYS share ≥2 vertices.
  5+5=10>6: ALWAYS share ≥4 vertices.
  Therefore alpha_2 at n=6 = #complementary both-cyclic pairs (weighted).

--- Verify: alpha_2 = weighted comp pair count ---
  CONFIRMED: alpha_2 = weighted complementary pair count at n=6

--- KEY: When are complementary 3-cycles both cyclic? ---
  Min t₃ with both-cyclic comp pair: 2
